Akure- Ondo State government on Tuesday donated a storey building to the Nigeria Police Zone 17 as the Headquarters. The building located opposite Federal College of Agriculture at Ijapo Estate, Akure, the state capital, would serve as operational office complex of the Zone 17. Handing over the building to the newly promoted Deputy Inspector of General of Police, Mr. David Folawiyo, the pioneer AIG of the zone, Governor Oluwarotimi Akeredolu disclosed that the decision of the DIG in accepting the location for the headquarters complex made it possible to locate it in Akure. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He appreciated President Muhammadu Buhari for approving the creation of the zone for grassroots policing and enhancing security of life and property of residents of Ondo and Ekiti states. “I must thank Nigeria Police for what they have done for us thus so far. The EndSARS has much impact on the psyche of the police. We owe it a duty to apologise and encourage the police so that they can come out to carry out their responsibilities.” NIMC Adopts Booking System For NIN Enrolment Fire Outbreak: Senator Bomai Donates N2million To Victims The governor appealed to the Police to come out and continue to enforce law and order in the state. Appreciating the police for the collaborative efforts with the South-West Security Network, which he said was not meant to rival any existing security agency, Governor Akeredolu noted that Police didn’t have enough men, but Amotekun can support them when necessary. He, however, disclosed the Amotekun Corps would recruit more men in 2021 to enhance it strength and performance. The governor, therefore, assured to continue to give all necessarily support to the Police for the protection of people of Ondo and Ekiti states. In his address, the DIG explained that Zone 17 was created on May 27, 2020 for Ondo and Ekiti states to serve the people better by coordinating and supervising the all commands in the zone. He appreciated Governor Akeredolu for renovating and donating the structure on time. Folawiyo also disclosed that Governor Kayode Fayemi of Ekiti State has promised to equip the headquarters with computer sets and other necessary gadgets. He, however, declared that community policing would be rigorously pursued, adding that the Zone would serve the people better by collaborating with other sister agencies. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION